With scissors, cut cartons from Breyers(R) All Natural Chocolate Ice Cream. Arrange Ice Cream on its side, then cut each into 4 lengthwise slices. In 13 X 9-inch baking dish, arrange 4 Ice Cream slices, pressing to form an even layer. Top with fruit, then remaining 4 Ice Cream slices, pressing to form an even layer. Cover and freeze 5 hours or overnight. Just before serving, top with whipped cream, smoothing with spatula. Arrange berries in flag pattern, with blueberries in upper left corner and 7 raspberry 'stripes'.